Setting multiple layers
Delete the code in the  that was written in the previous step, and then proceed with the following procedure. Here, the material explains a method for loading multiple tile layers and switching between them in the map window. In this section, learners can attempt to import an aerial photographs tile provided by the Geospatial Information Authority of Japan.
const basemap = L.tileLayer('https://tile.openstreetmap.org/{z}/{x}/{y}.png', {
        maxZoom: 19,
        attribution: '&copy; OpenStreetMap'
    })

const addmap1 = L.tileLayer('https://cyberjapandata.gsi.go.jp/xyz/ort/{z}/{x}/{y}.jpg', {
maxZoom: 18,
attribution: "GSI maps"
});

const webmap = L.map('map',{
    center:[34.9849,135.7586],
    zoom:14,
    layers:[basemap] //A layer is displayed when the map is opened.
});

//Grouping tile layers
const maps = {
"OSM":basemap,
"Aerial photo（2007～）":addmap1
};

// Setting layer selecting box
L.control.layers(maps).addTo(webmap);

